section.section:
A hospital shall be classified:
As a general hospital if the hospital at least has the facilities and provides the services that are necessary for the general medical and surgical care of patients;
As a special hospital if the hospital:
Defines a program of specialized services, such as obstetrics, mental health, tuberculosis, orthopedy, chronic disease, or communicable disease;
Admits only patients with medical or surgical needs within the program; and
Has the facilities for and provides those specialized services;
As a special rehabilitation hospital if the hospital meets the requirements of this subtitle and Subtitle 12 of this title; or
As a limited service hospital if the health care facility:
Is licensed as a hospital on or after January 1, 1999;
Changes the type or scope of services offered by eliminating the capability to admit or retain individuals for overnight hospitalization;
Retains an emergency or urgent care center; and
Complies with the regulations adopted by the Secretary under § 19-307.1 of this subtitle.

text.section:
A related institution shall be classified:
As a care home if the related institution provides care to individuals who, because of advanced age or physical or mental disability, require domiciliary care or personal care in a protective environment; or
As a nursing home if the related institution:
Provides nursing care for chronically ill or convalescent patients; or
Offers to provide 24-hour a day nursing care of patients in a home-type facility such as:
A convalescent home;
A nursing unit of a home for the aged;
A psychiatric nursing home;
A nursing facility for individuals with disabilities;
A home for alcoholics; or
A halfway house.
